node.text:
Today we’re taking it to the field. You can also do this on a treadmill

1. 50 meter sprint 
-25 push ups
2. 50 meter sprint 
-8 cycle jumps each leg
3. 50 meter sprint 
-15 V ups
4. 50 meter sprint 
-7 broad jumps 
5. 50 meter sprint 
-30 shoulder taps.
6. 50 meter sprint 
-10 burpees jumps 

Rest 3 mins and repeat 2 more times.
@fitnessculturetraining @gymshark 
🎥 @alexluscombe_photography 
Song Astronaut in the Ocean by Masked Wolf #trackworkout #hiitworkout #fatlosscardio #circuittraining

node.text:
Quick, easy, and can be done anywhere. 
100 air squats
100 push-ups
100 sit ups. 
It’s amazing how something so simple can leave you wiped out!

node.title: Love him or hate him, Tag your favorite “GYM BRO”

node.text:
Intimate back day - just me, you and the weights!
We’ve all heard you got to “Row to Grow”, I would agree with this and even go further and say that bent over rows are the ultimate upper body movement! It works the muscles in the back, shoulders, core and even posterior chain. Lot of neurological connection goin on as we stabilize as we strengthen! 

Bent  over row(35 degrees) - 10,8,8,6. Limit the amount of lower back movement.

Single arm DB row - 12,10,8. Pull to the hip.

Batwing incline row- keep it light and concentrate on pull with rest delt. 8,8,8

Leaning lay pull down. Making this more of a row by leaning back. 10,10,10.

Supine cable low to high row. Love this for the lower Lats. 
10,10,10

@fitnessculturetraining 
@gymshark

node.text:
20 years ago a 16 year old me was eating breakfast before school when we got the news that a plane crashed into the World Trade North tower. The world stood still that day. As we watched the events unfold on TV like the rest of the world, one thing I vividly remember was the feeling of unity. People came together as AMERICANS. Everything that could’ve divided us paled in comparison to everything that UNITED us. It’s amazing what happens when everyone comes together with a common goal. This picture embodies that to me. I’ll never forgot that day, the ones we lost, the hero’s, and feeling of a very “UNITED”STATES OF AMERICA 🇺🇸 
Where were you on 9-11-2001.
Pic- @cole

node.text:
This was a great shoulder workout! From the heavy first movement to the higher volume, all around GREAT WORKOUT! Swipe and save! 

1️⃣Smith Machine behind the neck press. 2 count eccentric. 10,8,8,6

2️⃣a. standing alternating DB raise. 3x 10 reps. Lots of time under tension.
2️⃣b. Cuban press 3 x 6 reps 

3️⃣a. EZ bar front raise 3x 8 reps 
3️⃣b. Rope race pulls 3 x 12 reps 

4️⃣standing cable raise (10-15 reps) once you fails go strait to 🔽
4️⃣bemt over rear raise (10-15 reps) 
Repeat 2 times

Shorts (2 in 1, 5 inch speed collection) @gymshark size large. 
Shoes - Nike metcon @wit.fitness 
@whoop

node.text:
This workout was shared with me by one of my followers to honor (workout from @wegohome) the 13 US military personnel that died in the Kabul Bombings serving their country.

5 rounds
13 med ball slams 
13 hand release pushups 
13 kettlebell (Russian) swings 
13 pulls ups
13 air squats 
13 mountain climbers (each side)
13 prisoner squats 
13 dips
13 box jumps 
13 push press 
13 chin up
13 sit ups
13 burpees 

Honoring 
-Sgt. Johanny Rosario Pichardo, 25, of Lawrence, Massachusetts

-Sgt. Nicole L. Gee, 23, of Sacramento, California

-Staff Sgt. Darin T. Hoover, 31, of Salt Lake City

Cpl. Hunter Lopez, 22, of Indio, California

Cpl. Daegan W. Page, 23, of Omaha, Nebraska

Cpl. Humberto A. Sanchez, 22, of Logansport, Indiana

Lance Cpl. David L. Espinoza, 20, of Rio Bravo, Texas

Lance Cpl. Jared M. Schmitz, 20, of St. Charles, Missouri

Lance Cpl. Rylee J. McCollum, 20, of Jackson, Wyoming

Lance Cpl. Dylan R. Merola, 20, of Rancho Cucamonga, California

Lance Cpl. Kareem M. Nikoui, 20, of Norco, California.

Navy Corpsman Maxton W. Soviak, 22, of Berlin Heights, Ohio

Staff Sgt. Ryan C. Knauss, 23, of Corryton, Tennessee

Thigh guy summer is extended this year due to the weather here in Mexico.
@representclo

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Steve Cook on August 23, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, biceps and indoor.

node.text:
Legs Legs Legs! Always enjoyed getting through a leg workout. Well balanceds legs don’t happen by chance. Proper training and consistency. Swipe and save! 

1. Shark squats (can sun in back squats. 
3x12 reps + 8 reps after a 15 second pause. 2 mins rest.

2a good morning 3 x 8
Superset
2b barbell step ups. 3 x 8.

3a leg press 3 x 12. 3 second eccentric.
Superset 
3b leg extension 3 x 15 reps

Training program - @fitnessculturetraining 
Shirt 
@gymshark
